In a meeting discussing artificial intelligence (AI), President Biden expresses his appreciation for the panel guests and the possibilities that AI brings. He acknowledges that AI can help address challenges like disease and climate change but also emphasizes the need to address potential risks to society, the economy, and national security. He mentions a proposed bill of rights for AI systems and the importance of responsible innovation and appropriate safeguards. The President highlights the responsibility of tech companies to ensure the safety of their products and mentions the harmful impact of powerful technologies without proper safeguards. He calls on Congress to pass bipartisan privacy legislation that limits personal data collection, bans targeted advertising to children, and prioritizes health and safety in product development. When asked if he thinks AI is dangerous, President Biden states that it remains to be seen.